ers\" title=\"Brynden Rivers\">Brynden<br />Rivers</a></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Shiera_Seastar\" title=\"Shiera Seastar\">Shiera<br />Seastar</a></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td></tr><tr align=\"center\"></tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p><br />\nOthers characters could be part of the Great Bastards as well, such as:\n</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Bellenora_Otherys\" title=\"Bellenora Otherys\">Bellenora Otherys</a> (b. <a href=\"/index.php/161_AC\" title=\"161 AC\">161</a>–<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_170_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">170&#160;AC</a>), <a href=\"/index.php/Narha_Otherys\" title=\"Narha Otherys\">Narha Otherys</a> (b. <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_162_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">162</a>–<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_171_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">171&#160;AC</a>), and <a href=\"/index.php/Balerion_Otherys\" title=\"Balerion Otherys\">Balerion Otherys</a> (b. <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_163_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">163</a>–<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_172_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">172&#160;AC</a>), the <a href=\"/index.php/Bastards\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastards\">bastards</a> of Aegon IV by <a href=\"/index.php/Bellegere_Otherys\" title=\"Bellegere Otherys\">Bellegere Otherys</a>. Bellegere was the daughter of a son of a <a href=\"/index.php/Sealord_of_Braavos\" title=\"Sealord of Braavos\">Sealord of Braavos</a> and a <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Islander\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Summer Islander\">Summer Islander</a> princess.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwow.5B.5Bmercy_.28the_winds_of_winter.29.7Cmercy.5D.5D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwow.5B.5Bmercy_.28the_winds_of_winter.29.7Cmercy.5D.5D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> However, we currently do not know if her parents were married and thus if Bellegere herself can be counted as a noblewoman or not.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_Plumm\" title=\"Viserys Plumm\">Viserys Plumm</a> (b. <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_176_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">176&#160;AC</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_177_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">177&#160;AC</a>) is rumored to be the son of Aegon by his cousin Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Elaena_Targaryen\" title=\"Elaena Targaryen\">Elaena Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_baelor_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_baelor_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Another rumor claims that Aegon had bastards with all three of <a href=\"/index.php/Butterwell_(Hand_of_the_King)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Butterwell (Hand of the King)\">Lord Butterwell</a>'s daughters.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Great_Bastards&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Targaryen Kings: Aegon IV.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwow.5B.5Bmercy_.28the_winds_of_winter.29.7Cmercy.5D.5D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwow.5B.5Bmercy_.28the_winds_of_winter.29.7Cmercy.5D.5D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Winds_of_Winter\" title=\"The Winds of Winter\">The Winds of Winter</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Winds_of_Winter-Chapte